Approximately 20-30% of patients later require intensive care and mechanical respiratory assistance.
In addition to the lower respiratory pathways, several organs, including gastrointestinal tube, liver and kidney, can also be infected in these severe cases, usually accompanied by a storm of cytokines, which could be fatal, particularly in immunodepressed patients.
