On 11 February 2020, the test was registered by the Federal Medical Care Monitoring Service. On 12 March 2020, it was reported that Mayo Clinic had developed a test to detect the infection by COVID-19. On 13 March 2020, Roche Diagnostics received FDA approval for a test that could take place within 3.5 hours in large volume, allowing a machine to perform approximately 4128 tests within 24 hours.
